The paper deals with distributed algorithms for testing and correcting graph properties, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The algorithms are designed for testing various graph properties such as bipartiteness, cycle-freeness, and exclusion of certain subgraphs, which are topics in graph theory and combinatorics (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the CONGEST-model, which is a popular model for distributed computing in computer networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity of the algorithms in terms of the number of processors in the network, which is a topic in network science and computer networks (cs.NI).
